A pharmaceutical company is developing a stability-indicating HPLC method for a drug substance that degrades via hydrolysis, oxidation, and photolysis. The compound is a weak base with a pKa of 8.5. During forced degradation studies, 6 degradation products were detected. Explain how you would design the chromatographic conditions to resolve all degradation products from the parent compound, ensure the method is stability-indicating per ICH Q1A guidelines, and what statistical criteria you would use to prove peak purity and confirm that co-elution is not occurring.
